                    <p class="privacy-policy-title">Privacy Policy</p>
                    <p>VMeet Privacy Policy</p>
                    <p>
                        This Privacy Policy explains how VMeet collects, uses, and protects your personal information
                        when
                        you use our services. By accessing or using VMeet, you agree to the terms described in this
                        policy.
                    </p>
                    <br>
    
                    <p>1. Information We Collect</p>
                    <p>When you use VMeet, we may collect the following types of information:</p>
                    <ul class="privacy-list">
                        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email address, and any other details you provide
                            when signing up or using the service.</li>
                        <li><strong>Meeting Information:</strong> Details about meetings you schedule, join, or host using
                            VMeet.</li>
                        <li><strong>Google Calendar Access:</strong> If you sign in with your Google account, VMeet will
                            request permission to access your Google Calendar in order to sync meeting schedules.</li>
                        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you use VMeet, such as features used,
                            meeting duration, and device/browser information.</li>
                    </ul>
    
                    <br>
                    <p>2. How We Use Your Information</p>
                    <p>We use your information to:</p>
                    <ul class="privacy-list">
                        <li>Provide, operate, and improve VMeet.</li>
                        <li>Schedule and manage meetings efficiently.</li>
                        <li>Sync your meeting schedules with Google Calendar (if connected).</li>
                        <li>Respond to customer service requests.</li>
                        <li>Maintain security and prevent fraudulent activities.</li>
                    </ul>
    
                    <br>
                    <p>3. Data Security</p>
                    <p>
                        We implement industry-standard measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure,
                        alteration, or destruction. However, no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.
                    </p>
    
                    <br>
                    <p>4. Your Rights</p>
                    <p>You may request to:</p>
                    <ul class="privacy-list">
                        <li>Access, update, or delete your personal information.</li>
                        <li>Disconnect your Google Calendar integration at any time.</li>
                    </ul>
    
                    <br>
                    <p>5. Changes to This Privacy Policy</p>
                    <p>
                        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an
                        updated
                        effective date.
                    </p>
